## Hints for Future Agents
- The onClickCapture approach (capture phase, stop propagation on container) is the correct way to prevent Link navigation after a drag. React's synthetic capture fires before children's bubble. wasDragging ref is a non-state ref to avoid re-renders.
- e.pointerType === "touch" guard is critical — removing it would break native mobile scroll (setPointerCapture grabs all touch events).
- The always-cream prompt box uses style={{ color: "var(--game-canvas-dark)", borderColor: "var(--game-canvas-dark)" }} intentionally — --game-ink flips to cream in dark mode (see #70), so inline style pinning to --game-canvas-dark (always dark) is the correct approach. Don't replace with className.

## Codebase Discoveries
- globals.css defines .game-card with box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--game-ink) — containers with overflow need pb-3+ to avoid clipping this shadow.
- RoundHighlightsCarousel already had sm:snap-x sm:snap-mandatory for CSS snapping on desktop — pointer drag supplements it (will still snap at card boundaries).

